history.content:
At Girls Teaching Girls to Code (GTC), we empower college girls pursuing Computer Science and Engineering to connect with local high school girls and inspire them through mentorship and applied projects. Throughout the school year, we host events to extend the influence of women in technology and inspire young girls to pursue their interests in tech.
We hope that you find the mission inspiring and invite you to join us in empowering women in tech!
                 
We are currently recruiting for People's Lead, Events/Social Lead, and Curriculum Lead. All details about recruitment and our club are in the application (due SEPTEMBER 8TH at 11:59 PST).
           
If you have more questions about GTC, you can go to our website at https://www.girlsteachinggirlstocode.org/ or come chat with us at Calapalooza on September 4th between 4 - 6 PM PST to learn about our club!
